This paper is about Machine Translation (MT) and user experience, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses user trust, which is related to Human-Computer Interaction (HCI), making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely sub-category. The paper uses a survey to collect data, which involves statistical analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the quality of translations, which is related to Information Retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a pilot study to test a hypothesis, which involves experimental design and analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
